cards.title:
Travertino Titanium is a unique limestone, formed near hot springs and waterfalls. The hot water from these springs dissolves lime, which, as the water cools—particularly around waterfalls—settles and deposits onto existing limestone layers.
This natural process creates Travertino Titanium, a brown-grey compact limestone (travertine) with distinctive characteristics. Its appearance is marked by pronounced, dark linear structures that create a banded, horizontal pattern.
cards.alt_text:
